 Accounting Ledger Application
  Overview

This is a Java Command-Line Interface (CLI) application that allows users to track financial transactions such as deposits and payments.

The application stores all transactions in a CSV file and allows users to view, filter, and generate reports based on the data.

Features
Home Screen
Add Deposit
Make Payment (Debit)
View Ledger
Exit Application
 Ledger
View all transactions (newest first)
Filter deposits only
Filter payments only
Clean table-style display (Excel-like formatting)
 Reports
Month-To-Date transactions
Year-To-Date transactions
Search by vendor or keyword
 Data Storage

All transactions are stored in:

src/main/resources/transactions.csv

Each transaction follows this format:

date|time|description|vendor|amount

Example:

2026-04-28|16:43:45|pen|Amazon|2.00
2026-04-28|16:46:24|bill|water|-23.00
🛠️ Technologies Used
Java (JDK 17)
File I/O (FileReader, FileWriter)
ArrayList
LocalDate and LocalTime
CLI (Console-based UI)
 How to Run
Clone the repository:https://github.com/Zebibm/Capstone1_Mohammed

Open the project in IntelliJ IDEA (or any Java IDE)
Run:
Main.java
Use the menu options in the console to interact with the application
